How will be the Mapping matrix if we have 3 levels of hierarchy? Do we need to put intermediate nodes as well as columns? or it will always be the lowest-level nodes only?

Example :
total -> {cat1, cat2}

cat1 -> {sub_cat1, sub_cat2, sub_cat3}
sub_cat1 - > {c1, c2}
sub_cat2 - > {c3, c4}
sub_cat3 - > {c5, c6}

cat2 -> {sub_cat4, sub_cat5}
sub_cat4 --> {c7, c8}
sub_cat5 --> {c9, c10}

For example - In the above scenario, do we have to keep all the lower levels (c1,c2,c3,c4,c5,c6,c7,c8,c9,c10) as columns in the Mapping matrix? or do I need to keep sub_catogory nodes (sub_cat1, sub_cat2, sub_cat3,sub_cat4, sub_cat5) as well in columns of Mapping matrix ?

Please Help on this...
